## purpose
Defines core runtime handling for social.

## runtime_scope
Runtime covers social visibility,
participation-aware display,
public/private rendering,
historical social reference,
and safe failure rendering.

## validation_rules
- social context must resolve
- participation basis must resolve
- public/private scope must resolve
- disclosure scope must be valid

## failure_modes
- invalid social context
- invalid participation basis
- invalid private/public scope
- safe runtime fallback

## observability
Runtime must emit enough signals
to distinguish social state,
participation scope,
visibility mode,
historical reference,
and failure surface.

## review_checklist
- social runtime scope is explicit
- public/private rendering is explicit
- failure handling is explicit
